{
  "stem": "4513.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were talking about Normandy--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was telling you.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And let me end-- I'll end up this with the 82nd.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So, the 80-- Eisenhower finally said, you're going into invasion.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We're going to take off.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You're going-- they had sent us down to the marshalling yards at Plymouth, which was the assembly area for the invasion. 82nd-- they sent them to wherever they sent them.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They stayed there.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's where they mounted their planes and they were taken over.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember seeing, that morning we-- that morning, before we went over, that they would-- there was a-- each one of those-- each one of their C-47s was pulling two gliders.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they were just-- air was filled with them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So and they say the paratroopers were inside the 47, the C-47s.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the glider troops were in the other one.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they were on their way to Normandy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We got on boats at night.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were on our way to Normandy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I've never seen so many boats in my whole life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, there were just thousands of them out there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the two big battleships were making runs down the coast when we got there, and-- and-- and bombing everything back up to try to soften up and get rid of the pill boxes.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- our job was to go ashore and to pull-- to pull-- take tape and clear paths up through the-- up through the hillside, so-- and get rid of all the anti-personnel mines that had been sewed in there.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that-- and with the tapes, the soldiers coming ashore behind us would know that this was a safe way to go up to the-- to the hills up above us.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We came into Omaha, what they call Omaha Red.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
